From 0aaf9d38c937cda9cb41b19a9429918fd9e7bcc2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Charlie Shao <charlie.shao@nordicsemi.no>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 09:37:23 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] [nrf noup] wifi: nrf70: add MSPI bus backend for sQSPI on
 nRF54LM20DK
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The nRF7002 Wi-Fi radio is normally connected over SPI. On nRF54LM20DK
with a hardware-modified nRF7002 EB-II (cut SB1-4, solder SB5-8), the
QSPI signals are available on the Port 2 SDP expansion header and can
be driven via the sQSPI (MSPI API) soft peripheral.

This commit adds:

bus/mspi_if.c+h:
  MSPI bus backend matching the existing spis_if.c API surface.
  - mspi_xfer_tx: quad write (PP4IO 0x38), 4-byte address
  - mspi_xfer_rx: quad read (READ4IO 0xEB), 4-byte address, 6 dummy
  - mspi_reg_write/read: single-wire at user-specified frequency
  - mspi_cmd_rpu_wakeup_fn: 8 MHz single write to reg 0x3F
  - mspi_validate_rpu_wake_writecmd: poll 0x2F for RPU_WAKEUP_NOW
  - mspi_wait_while_rpu_awake: poll 0x1F for RPU_AWAKE_BIT

bus/Kconfig, bus/CMakeLists.txt:
  Add NRF70_ON_MSPI symbol; build mspi_if.c when selected.

bus/device.c, bus/rpu_hw_if.c:
  Wire MSPI bus backend into existing bus abstraction layer.

Kconfig.nrfwifi:
  Expose NRF70_ON_MSPI as a visible option.

dts/bindings/wifi/nordic,nrf70-mspi.yaml:
dts/bindings/wifi/nordic,nrf7002-mspi.yaml:
  DTS bindings for MSPI bus node and nRF7002 device node.

boards/shields/nrf7002eb2_mspi/:
  Shield for nRF54LM20DK + modified nRF7002 EB-II:
  - softperipheral_ram at 0x2007c000 (16 KB carved from cpuapp SRAM)
  - sqspi@3b40 register file, nrf7002-mspi@0 at 32 MHz quad 1-4-4
  - Board overlay: 496 KB cpuapp_sram, Port 2 pinctrl, UART30 console

Tested on nRF54LM20DK + nRF7002 EB-II at 32 MHz:
20/20 consecutive boot→WiFi-connect cycles pass.

Assisted-by: Claude:claude-sonnet-4.6
Signed-off-by: chsh <chsh@users.noreply.github.com>
Signed-off-by: Charlie Shao <charlie.shao@nordicsemi.no>
